article.headline: New Hampshire 62, Albany, N.Y. 53
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Alvin Abreu scored 22 points and Tyrone Conley added 12, leading New Hampshire to a 62-53 win over Albany (N.Y.) on Tuesday night. Abreu also led the way from 3-point range for New Hampshire (9-13, 4-7 America East Conference), knocking down three long-range shots. Conley and Colbey Santos connected on a pair of 3-pointers apiece for the Wildcats, who finished 7-for-14 from beyond the arc (50 percent). The Great Danes were just 1-for-13 from 3-point range (7.7 percent). Albany went on a 5-0 run to open the game, but the Wildcats put together a 12-0 run, capped by back-to-back 3-pointers by Conley, and never trailed again. New Hampshire led by five points at the break and outscored Albany 35-31 to seal it in the second half. Mike Black and Fran Urli scored 14 points apiece to pace the Great Danes (6-21, 1-11), who have lost eight straight games.
